The rand firmed against the dollar early on Wednesday, extending its recovery into a second day as the greenback edged lower against a basket of currencies. At 0626 GMT, the rand traded at 13.32 per dollar, 0.11% firmer than its overnight close. The dollar fell 0.12% against a basket of six currencies and was at 95.101. “This morning emerging market currencies generally firmer as the (People’s Bank of China) suggested that further weakness in the Yuan was not a one way bet, and the dollar lost ground against the majors as well,” Nedbank analysts said in a note. They added: “Locally the markets head into a public holiday, as a result liquidity likely to be tested.” South African financial markets will be closed on Thursday for a public holiday.